
<title>Exponential growth and decay modeled by discrete dynamical systems</title>

<description>
Overview of exponential growth and decay in discrete time.  Exploration of their qualitative properties as well as solutions to the dynamical system.
</description>

<p>The 
<ref uri='doenet:doenetId=nzSdVA_gPhe5W-oM4IN5z'>solution to a linear discrete dynamical system</ref>
 is an exponential.  If we choose conditions so that the 
<ref uri='doenet:state_variable|page_type=definition'>state variable</ref>
 stays positive, this exponential solution will exhibit either exponential growth or exponential decay.  We can determine whether we get growth or decay from the parameters of the system.</p>




