<math name='base' simplify='full'>$a</math>
<math name='base_to_the_n' simplify='full' >$base ^$n </math>
</setup>

<p>For the discrete dynamical system
<md>
  <mrow>$x _{ $n  +1}\amp = $a  $x _{ $n  }</mrow>
  <mrow>$x _{0}\amp = $x0 </mrow>
</md>
for what range of values of the parameter <m>$a </m> does the system exhibit exponential decay?</p>

<p>
<answer symbolicEquality>0</answer>
 <m>\lt $a  \lt</m> 
<answer symbolicEquality>1</answer>
</p>

<p>For what range of values of the parameter <m>$a </m> does the system exhibit exponential growth?</p>

<p><m>$a  \gt</m> 
<answer symbolicEquality>1</answer>
</p>


<solution>
<p>We can answer this question by solving the system. The equation is already in function iteration form.
To go from <m>$x _{ $n  }</m> to <m>$x _{ $n +1}</m>, we must multiply by <m>$base </m>.  Since the initial condition is <m>$x _0 = $x0 </m>, and we must multiply by <m>$base </m> for a total of <m>$n </m> times to get to <m>$x _{ $n  }</m>,  the solution is
<me>$x _{ $n  } = $base_to_the_n $x0 .</me></p>

<p>For exponential decay we need
<me>0 \lt $base  \lt 1.</me>

</p>

<p>For exponential growth, we need
<me>$base  \gt 1.</me>
</p>

</solution>


