<problem newNamespace>
<title>Parameter regime for exponential growth/decay, difference form</title>

<setup>

<selectFromSequence assignNames='x0' from='0.1' to=' 10' step=' 0.1'/>
<select assignNames='x' >x y z s u v w </select>
<select assignNames='n' >n t </select>
<select assignNames='a' >a b c alpha beta gamma </select>
<math name='base' simplify='full'>$a +1</math>
<math name='base_to_the_n' simplify='full' >$base ^$n </math>
</setup>


<p>For the discrete dynamical system
<md>
  <mrow>
$x _{ $n  +1} - $x _{ $n  }\amp = $a  $x _{ $n  }  
</mrow>
  <mrow>$x _{0}\amp = $x0 </mrow>
</md>
for what range of values of the parameter <m>$a </m> does the system exhibit exponential decay?</p>

<p>
<answer symbolicEquality>-1</answer>
 <m>\lt $a  \lt</m> 
<answer symbolicEquality>0</answer>
</p>

<p>For what range of values of the parameter <m>$a </m> does the system exhibit exponential growth?</p>

<p><m>$a  \gt</m> 
<answer symbolicEquality>0</answer>
</p>


<solution>
<p>We can answer this question by solving the system. 
Since the equation is in difference form, we add <m>$x _{ $n  }</m> to both sides, rewriting the equation in function iteration form as <me>$x _{ $n  +1} = ($a +1)$x _$n .</me>

To go from <m>$x _{ $n  }</m> to <m>$x _{ $n +1}</m>, we must multiply by <m>$base </m>.  Since the initial condition is <m>$x _0 = $x0 </m>, and we must multiply by <m>$base </m> for a total of <m>$n </m> times to get to <m>$x _{ $n  }</m>,  the solution is
<me>$x _{ $n  } = $base_to_the_n $x0 .</me></p>

<p>For exponential decay we need
<me>0 \lt $base  \lt 1.</me>
This condition is the same as <me>-1 \lt $a  \lt 0.</me>
</p>

<p>For exponential growth, we need
<me>$base  \gt 1.</me>
This condition is the same as <me>$a > 0.</me>
</p>



</solution>

</problem>




